caption: This place is consistently amazing! Favorites are the Tacos De Carnitas and the Pulpo!  Frozen margaritas are excellent as well! Highly recommend!

The place is great the environment great vibe was seated very fast the food is amazing and drinks are good too but with my last visit I was really displeased by the waiter once the bill was paid i spent almost 150$ he tried to bully me and pressure me and lie saying it’s the law that I have to tip him 30$ and once I told him I could only give what I could he began to belittle my tip saying it wasn’t enough for him which is really unprofessional and to truly honest distasteful and ruined my experience at this location before all of this Me and my girlfriend enjoyed our time just wish I could of left with the same inviting energy that I was greeted with.....

Oh man! I had great expectations for this place. Not worth the hype... for the food. Red enchiladas were probably the most boring of all enchiladas I’ve ever tasted. Sauce was watered down. Not even authentic mole. Cheese didn’t make justice. So bland and un creative in every way. Rice and beans had same result. Nothing memorable about it. Just plain boring. Drinks... well that’s another story. Drinks were well done with great flavor. 2 stars for drinks and friendly staff. Food needs to be revamped.
I had a superb experience at this place. We liked the great vibes and the meals. The staff members were super affable. I am content we ultimately managed to eat here.

This is by far my favorite place to grab dinner. The food is consistently fantastic, the drinks are generous, and the people are absolutely wonderful! I couldn’t recommend this place more, it has become my go to weekend spot!

My wife and I discovered this place recently.  We've been on the hunt for a good Mexican restaurant that is fairly close to the C / B subway line in the 125th to 81st street area.  Tried a bunch and Rancho Tequileria made the top of the list for us.  We've tried quite a few items on the menu over the past few months.  Our go-to order is now pretty much the nachos and the carne assada tacos.  The nachos are really quite taste - my wife loves them.  And the carne assada tacos are wonderful.  I also love their Jumbo margaritas.  The environment is very welcoming and the staff is super friendly.

Smh we were then seated and ordered from the lunch menu. We noticed that no one was ordering food and was wondering why. Now we know the drinks are the bomb and the food is ok. Come here if you want to "party on" the food could be better. I had the chicken quesadillas and it had a hint of floral taste which was off putting. Stick to the drinks and maybe an appetizer.

My fiancé and I visited this restaurant on Monday June 29th and sat outside due to covid and social distancing. all seemed nice until we ordered Azteca quesadilla which contains steak, chicken and shrimp. My fiancé clearly told the waiter “no shrimp” as he is allergic. After a few bites we notice there was shrimp in the quesadilla. To top everything off it started raining and then hailing which I immediately told my fiancé let’s go inside the restaurant. A minute later the restaurants awning fell to the ground. Luckily we were inside. Later that night my fiancé became ill and was covered in hives and swelled up. He had shortness of breath and could have lost his life. We will never again visit a restaurant in which the employees can not follow instructions especially when involving food allergies.

Simply excellent. The Chile Relleno was near perfect in taste (great vegetarian dish). Not overdone on the seasoning while still full of savory flavor. Texture of the pepper plus the other ingredients was top notch.  The drinks also aren't over-sweetened so much that you want to scrape sugar off your tongue. Get it frozen, I don't usually order margs that way but I loved theirs. Everything seemed to be done just right. Hope this restaurant does well for many years to come!

I celebrated my birthday today in this great restaurant. happy to tell that we had a sensational evening and the restaurant was undoubtedly one of the reasons for that happy gathering. The waiters  contributed in a sweet manner, the cooking was extremely good and my buddies were so  thrilled. We shall no dout come back again for more celebrations. thanks very much.

Traditional Mexican fare. Good quality food. Full bar. Good martinis. Friendly, competent staff. I find the food a bit slow to come out, but it's nothing problematic. The place is often packed, and therefore loud, so if that bothers you or you're not in the mood for that, perhaps go elsewhere that night. Otherwise, you should definitely try it. You'll probably want to go back.
food was average.. and very friendly service...

Okay plus, really. Nice ambience, festive, but the food was just average Mexican. And the margarita needed more Cointreau or Grand Marnier. Noche Mexicana up the street is much more authentic and flavorful, but not as nice a place to sit.

Last week, I had the best quesadilla of my life here! Normally, the best thing about a quesadilla is melted cheese, bc there's nothing on Earth better than that. But the chicken and Pico de Gallo of this quesadilla somehow outshined melty cheese and sour cream. Unbelievable! And for $11! With a lovely salad!

Nice staff, food was cool, prices were inflated imo, cheaper food and more portions in midtown, but the staff was so cool i thought this mfer was gonna pull up a chair and chill. the jalapeno poppers come 7 a dish. guac is fresher than my uncle’s ashes right out the cremation & the soup was aight, tastes like it wasent meant for flavor. im probably thinking too hard but for a mexican place i rather bring my people uptown. maybe its for the no salt no gluten crowd because they ruin everything lol. Only 4 stars because the prices were a little steep but blame the landlord for that right? 😂

This place became a great dissapointment.  We made reservations and our friend arrived first, maybe 3-5 minutes before we arrived and they refused to seat her because we where not all together.  Is ridicules otherwise why make reservations.  Tables where open and available when we did come in.  Needless to say we left and will not be returning.

I actually stumbled upon this place on my way to get lunch somewhere nearby. I am so glad I changed plans and ate here!  What a great place! Friendly staff, great drinks, good food, awesome prices! The complementary chips and salsa were fresh and tasty. I had the burrito lunch special for $10.95 and it included soup or salad. I had tortilla soup.  If you like a little extra kick, be sure to request some of the made in house hot sauce. Yum!  I can't wait to go back and try more things from the menu!

Firstly, the ambience is amazing, from the staff to the design- brick walls, lighting, colors, etc. The food AND drinks are spectacular! I went there weeks ago with a friend and as picky as we are, there was absolutely no complaints between us both. I ordered the steak enchiladas, soooo good! My friend had the steak quesadilla, 👍👍👍  We learned while there that the restaurant had just opened up the week before. To be a brand new establishment and have service and food that amazing is rare! We are heading back to the restaurant tomorrow! 😊😊 Folks, do yourself a favor and visit this restaurant then come back and post a review. Definitely, well deserved! DELISH!!!
